    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This is yet another instance where we see it's better to rely on the [`data` field for the payload](https://firebase.google.com/docs/cloud-messaging/concept-options#notification-messages-with-optional-data-payload) instead of `notification` field (another being e.g. https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/3451). We should be sending a silent notification (only `data` filled in) and getting that to trigger an intent on our mobile app, which would be responsible for decoding the payload and actually displaying a localized message.",
