    "body": "@chadyj another thing we're sending in the PN as hidden metadata is the sender pubkey address and the chat-id (which in a 1:1 seems to be one of the interlocutor's pubkey address). Ideally, we'd want to send those values hashed (or maybe there's a better approach @corpetty?) and then do a lookup on the receiver end (same thing btw if we send a message ID, which we should add to the payload to enable current/future scenarios).\r\nIs it something we want to address in this PR as well (move to using hashes of addresses)?",
